      <div class="tl-day">Day 7</div>
      <div class="tl-work">Waterproofing membrane (2 coats + curing)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item">
      <div class="tl-day">Days 8‚Äì10</div>
      <div class="tl-work">Tiling ‚Äî floor, walls, shower</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item">
      <div class="tl-day">Days 11‚Äì12</div>
      <div class="tl-work">Ceiling, electrical fit-off</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item">
      <div class="tl-day">Days 13‚Äì14</div>
      <div class="tl-work">Fixtures, tapware, final clean & handover</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq">
  <div class="stag reveal">FAQ</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Common Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list reveal">
    <details class="faq-item" open>
      <summary>What does the Rs. 15,000/sq.ft rate include exactly?</summary>
      <p>All labour and materials for demolition, masonry, plumbing rough-in, waterproofing, electrical rough-in, tiling (adhesive, grout, leveling clips), ceiling installation, and fixture installation. It excludes tiles, bathware (toilet, basin, bathtub), and tapware ‚Äî those are supplied by you.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How is the bathroom area measured for the quote?</summary>
      <p>We measure the internal floor area of the bathroom in square feet. The final quote is based on this area plus a site visit assessment of the specific scope ‚Äî existing condition, wall heights, complexity of plumbing relocation, etc.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I supply my own plumber or electrician?</summary>
      <p>Our standard contract is all-inclusive ‚Äî splitting trades creates the coordination gaps we're trying to avoid. If you have a specific requirement, discuss it with us at the quoting stage and we can accommodate where possible.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What waterproofing system do you use?</summary>
      <p>We use a two-coat liquid membrane system applied to the full floor and walls to at least 1.8m height (or full height in shower areas). Reinforcement tape is applied at all floor-to-wall junctions. This is the highest-performance approach for Sri Lanka's climate.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you handle the permit/approval process?</summary>
      <p>Bathroom renovations within an existing footprint typically don't require planning approval in Sri Lanka. If your renovation involves structural changes or a building extension, you will need to consult your local authority ‚Äî we can advise on what your project requires.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What guarantee do you offer?</summary>
      <p>We provide a 12-month workmanship guarantee covering waterproofing, tiling, and all installation work. Structural defects attributable to our work will be rectified at no charge. We also source quality materials with manufacturer warranties where applicable.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

